<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-41-0308 </DOCNO><TEXT>We have investigated electron capture accompanied by nuclear scatteringby studying the probability for electron capture from /sup 22/Ne in thevicinity of the 1.510-MeV elastic nuclear resonance /sup 22/Ne(p,p)/sup22/Ne. We have found a large nuclear resonance effect in the probabilityfor electron capture. The data are in some disagreement with theoreticalcalculations by Jakubassa-Amundsen and Amundsen, based on the strong-potentialBorn approximation for electron capture.</TEXT></DOC>